abstract: New York Jets agree to pay $325,000 to settle lawsuit over wages with its cheerleaders.

headline.print_headline: Like Three N.F.L. Teams Before, Jets Settle a Wage Lawsuit Filed by Cheerleaders
headline.main: Jets Become Latest N.F.L. Team to Settle a Wage Lawsuit Filed by Cheerleaders

snippet: The Jets agreed to pay a total of $325,000 to 52 of the team’s dancers who worked from 2011 to 2013 for fixed pay that some said violated minimum wage laws.
lead_paragraph: The Jets agreed to pay a total of $325,000 to 52 of the team’s dancers who worked from 2011 to 2013 for fixed pay that some said violated minimum wage laws.
